<div class="postcell post-layout--right">
    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
                
<p>I am used to working in languages such as <code>C#</code>/<code>Java</code>/<code>Python</code> where each class would have its own file, and for a <strong>class</strong> to see other classes, you would <strong>import</strong> the package containing those classes. How does this work in <code>php</code>? The documentation shows you how to create classes, but I don't understand how it all fits together in a <code>php</code> context. I know of the include statement, which just sticks the files together basically.</p>
    </div>

