<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="12149149">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>As of PHP 5.3.0 , it is recommended that you use the spl_autoload_register() function because __autoload() is said to be deprecated some time in the future.</p>

<p>An easy way to use this function:</p>

<p>1) Place each class file into the 'classes' folder</p>

<p>2) Run an anonymous function inside spl_autoload_register() which specifies your class folder:</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">spl_autoload_register</span>(function (<span class="hljs-variable">$class</span>) {
    <span class="hljs-keyword">include</span> <span class="hljs-string">'classes/'</span> . <span class="hljs-variable">$class</span> . <span class="hljs-string">'.php'</span>;
});
</code></pre>

<p>Now when you try to use a class that is not defined in your code yet, it will check that class folder one last time before giving you an error.</p>
    </div>
