</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>Imagine you have been making your object in PHP in a file called myObject.php</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-meta">&lt;?php</span>

  <span class="hljs-class"><span class="hljs-keyword">class</span> <span class="hljs-title">myObject</span>
  </span>{
    <span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">__construct</span>(<span class="hljs-params"/>)
    </span>{
      <span class="hljs-keyword">echo</span> <span class="hljs-string">"Hello, World"</span>;
    }
  }

<span class="hljs-meta">?&gt;</span>
</code></pre>

<p>And in another file, you would like to use the object (let's call this myfile.php). You would have to include your object - like this:</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-meta">&lt;?php</span>

  <span class="hljs-keyword">include</span>(<span class="hljs-string">"myObject.php"</span>);

  <span class="hljs-variable">$intance</span> = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> <span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">myObject</span>();

<span class="hljs-meta">?&gt;</span>
</code></pre>

<p>Quite simple.</p>
    </div>
